SSyynnooppssiiss
       #include <unistd.h>

       int getdtablesize(void);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       Each  process  has  a  descriptor table, whose entries are
       numbered with small integers starting at 0.  The call get-
       dtablesize returns the current maximum size of this table.

       It is equivalent to a call to the  getrlimit  system  call
       with resource set to RLIMIT_NOFILE.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluuee
       The  getdtablesize function returns the current soft limit
       as  if  obtained  from  a  call  to  getrlimit  with   the
       RLIMIT_NOFILE resource set.

UUssaaggee
       There is no direct relationship between the value returned
       by getdtablesize and OPEN_MAX defined in limits.h.

